description: The US president will sign an executive order permitting use of the Department of War as a 'secondary title' for the sprawling department, a White House document said, apparently due to its official name being set in law. headline: France's Socialists present budget plan to navigate post-Bayrou era
description: The budget proposals put forward by the Socialists reveal a heightened sense of caution compared to previous left-wing estimates. They are intended to carry weight in upcoming discussions over the formation of a new government, ahead of Prime Minister François Bayrou's anticipated fall on Monday.

headline: NATO: Europe is caught in Trump's 'protection racket'
description: The Europeans, eager to keep the US from abandoning Ukraine, waver between submission and emancipation. Yet for Trump, who doesn't heed political or moral arguments, NATO must, above all, pay off, writes Le Monde columnist Alain Frachon.
